    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see what you mean, but it feels like those \"criticisms\" are mostly just things that happen when the transition isn't managed right, rather than being flaws in the concept itself. Like, if you have good transit, congestion isn't really an issue, right? It seems like the \"anti-density\" crowd is more focused on preserving a specific way of life that isn't even sustainable anymore. Is there actually any merit to their stance, or is it mostly just NIMBYism and resistance to change?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
